\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Mrs Deason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 And present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 146 Pomphlett Road, Plymstock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 And your marital status?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Widow I am.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When were you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What was the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 1898.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 In Torpoint. Yes. Yes, in Cornwall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh - well - about - twelve, fourteen years I suppose. Well before I was married, until I married you see in 1919. I lived over to Torpoint then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where did you move to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Plymouth. For the time being. Well - at Mountgo
ld in Plymouth. Then my husband was in the Navy you see and we went away, took the children with us. And then - after a couple of years we came back. The boys went to the grammar school in Plymouth. And - well - my husband had various - appointments you k
now in ships which I couldn't go because - of having the boys at the grammar school you see, and - what happens now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was this in Mountgold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, they went to - one went to Sutton High and one went to Devonport High, while I was living in Plymouth.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Then you moved from Mountgold to here did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Then - Mountgold out to - out here, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You've lived here ever since?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 And I've lived here thirty years. The boys have both married and - from here you see, and gone to various parts of - England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So really you lived in the Torpoint house until 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Well 'til I got married you see. Then we left there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Three sisters. Well one died at birth, but I had two sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How old were they, were they older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well I was the middle one, I've got one younger, which is a widow now and my oldest sister died - the same time as my husband, within a fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How much older than you was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Eighteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 And the younger one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh she's six years younger than me. That's why I'm going to make my home you see nearer her, for her to look after me really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh he died when I - I was - twelve when he died. Me mother was left a widow with three of us, you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you remember roughly how old he might be when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - well he was - he died when he was forty-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That would make him thirty-one when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where did he come from?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 He's Torpoint - too, yes, and he was in the Navy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What doing in the Navy, was it the Royal Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, the Royal Navy. Yes, he was a Warrant Officer in the Royal Navy. My father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did he always have that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh yes, he died - during his time in the Navy. He was home sick - he came home on leave - and he - he was taken sick and he - he died on his leave actually. Then my mother was left a widow with three of us. With a pension of nine shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 This is before the first world war even?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 There wouldn't be an awful}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10566803\charrsid14952291  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 lot of state assistance then would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well no, but you see, the main thing in Torpoint, our men Naval or dockyard, that is the - main thing over there 
you see. So they were both - I think that's why most of the boys went in the Navy, in my young days you know. There wasn't much else really for them. It wasn't like it is now you know. Of course it's still the main Naval port you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Is it near Devonport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Devonport. No, you - well Devonport's on the - the Devon side, and Torpoint's the Cornish side you see, with the Tamar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your father ever have any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No. Oh no, he was in the Navy all his time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So you can't remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, she was around about the same age as me father you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 About thirty-one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did she come from Torpoint as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Where - well you - you sort of intermixed and married from there see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did she have any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did she do any after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. That wasn't done in those days you know. No women went to work then, it was infra dig to go to work anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can I ask you about your life at home when you were a child, until you left school? How many rooms would there be in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well - you see - we had the house - to ourselves until my fathe
r died, and - then my mother had to let part of the house because she had a mortgage you see on it and - very little money coming in. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was it a big house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, no, seven rooms that's all, you see, not - so she kept three herself to make ends
 meet and let the other three and a half sort of you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Before your father died would there be sort of three receptions rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, we had - the house to ourself when he was alive you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would there be a reception room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes
, well just like the seven roomed house you know, the lounge and dining room and - well quite a nice house but then of course the funds went down to - as I say she was left with nine shillings a week pension, and no help from State or anything like that t
hen, she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where would she get the pension from, from the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, that was the Naval widow's pension as - as a Warrant Officer's widow she got that. Nine shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Which wasn't a lot really was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well she had hard going real
ly. Yes. And we were all schoolgirls you see. We didn't - of course there was no jobs then, well we were at school you see, we couldn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Before your father died did your parents have any of their brothers and sisters in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, eve
rybody had their own - little place you know usually then. That had any status at all. 'Course - there were other poorer people you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You say you didn't have lodgers until after your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No. She let the - the unfurnished flat,
 you see, to bring in the enough money to pay off her mortgage, but her house was only three hundred and fifty anyway. But of course that was a lot of money in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How many lodgers would there be then in the spare flat, just the one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh n
o, only one. Husband and wife you see. But they used to pay five shillings a week rent. Then, you see, I remember that. So that just helped her. Mm. But - as I say she - it was hard going but we seemed to get by you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house before your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No, no, she did her own work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, oh yes, light the copper, you know, it was a copper in the scullery, light the fire in under the copper to boil up and get th
e hot water. No such thing as - heaters of any description. We did have gas in the house. No we didn't. No, we didn't have any gas, oil lamps. See? So that - any heating had to come from - wood and - sticks and stuff you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about the clothes, did your mother or father mend or make the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh yes, mother used to make all our bits and pieces, having three girls you see. It was easier really than having - boys. She could make up little frocks and that for us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would the clothes be new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh no, we used to get - we had a little bit given us from an aunt that had no family, she used to help quite a lot. But - mother would contrive and - do you know different - then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So it was mainly pleasure as well, not having to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well, she had to do it as well you see. She had to do it because there was very little money coming in in those days you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was this before your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, after he died that was, because he was all right - they were all right while he was alive you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What would happen before he died, would she make the clothes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - she didn't have to do it then. But she used to do a bit because she enjoyed doing it. But she was no professional you know, 
not - no, she - she - just did it because - well I - something to do I suppose because other than that there's not very much to do. There was no pictures or - television or - nothing at all. She used to go to her church - we used to all go to Sunday schoo
l
 and that. And - during the week there was the Band of Hope and that was about all. No - well no amusements really, that's why - of course the children really were in the home more. Nowhere for 'em to go. And of course the street lighting was only - lamps
, that you - couldn't go very far. Oh it wasn't safe to be out really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where would she buy the clothes then before your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well she would buy bits of material at the shops you see, make up. And - you know if anybody liked to - give her a
 garment she'd cut it down and - well she had to do it, she wasn't a dressmaker by any means you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about shoes and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well that was - a problem, but of course - shoes were - five shillings a pair you know sort of but - and
 - with - with all us being girls we weren't very hard on shoes, you see not like boys really. But we - we got - well we used to wear buttoned boots, my sister and I, you know, when you were - of course you know they wouldn't dream of - having it now. But
 
of course we didn't earn any money you see 'cos being schoolgirls so we had to buy - have what was bought for us. There was no choice for the children like they are - today, choosing what they like and what they don't like. We had to - in fact I didn't ha
v
e a new garment for a very long time because I was just that bit smaller than my eldest sister, so she had the new and I had hers you see most times. It was quite a - day when I had anything new you see 'cos being - just the eighteen months younger than h
er you see I - took hers, because she had to be very careful of what she had because it had to come for me after. Yes. Yes. Oh dear yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your father help when he was at home, did he help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, he 
wasn't home very much really in the Navy you know they used to do - long commissions, different to what they do today you know. He was away quite a lot. He was in the home fleet - used to be home on leave a little bit, but - they used to try and make the 
most of that you know. And didn't - he didn't have a lot to do really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When he was home would he do anything like sort of cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh he'd handy - he was - he would help her do any little job like they do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would he ever do any cooking or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No, he wouldn't do it. No, not father. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about things like helping with the washing up or making the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, well he might do that but you see I was only twelve when he died. So much as I remember him, you kn
ow, on occasions, I - I don't - remember him doing a lot in the home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Any decorating or repairs,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, no, he didn't do that. No. I don't think the decorating was done too often, you know, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did he ever help you dress or bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh yes, he used to do the bathing, because we always remember all three of us - that he would - go at us every morning with our faces and necks you know with cold water, and of course we used to go nearly mad with that, because we always were pamper
ed to have warm water you see when - with mother. But he said, oh freshen you up, you know, he used to get hold of our - tops of our heads and - give us a good doing when he was home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where did you get the hot water from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well, the kettle because we had the stove, you know, the black}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10566803\charrsid14952291 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 lead stove. The range, kitchen range what they call 'em now, you see there was no such a thing as gas cookers or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would he ever take you out without your mother, go for walks or anything while he was home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well, possibly, but he was - liked to be home because when he was on leave he wanted to spend as much time with all of us you see.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you remember him reading to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. I don't think that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Ever tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well he's Naval man you know, he - he'd come up with a - few you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of stories would he tell you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Not that sort. Not Naval yarns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 If your mother ever went out would he look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, but then you see he wa
sn't home a lot really, to look after us, in fact there was the three of us you see that we could play round together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You say the other one was six years younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, my youngest sister was six and I was twelve when my sist - other one was four
teen when my father died you see. But - she - the fourteen, she was very good. She would stay with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have any tasks you had to regularly carry out at home to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You didn't have anything to do like that really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
No, he just came on leave and - we made the best of it and went out in the fields and things like that, because as I say - nothing else to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did the girls have any special tasks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. Well - we used to turn in a bit you
 know. All of us, we were brought to - clean the kitchen knives on a board, you know, there was no stainless steel or anything like that. And - my oldest sister used to - we used to have rabbits a lot you know in those days and - she would - skin the rabb
i
t and get the tuppence for the - skin you see. She was very helpful, my eldest sister. Although she wasn't - much older than me but - you see when my father died - she sort of was a companion to my mother more so than - myself and my youngest sister, we w
ere in one bedroom and she slept in the bedroom with mother you see. That she really was a companion to me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your older sister help you or the younger sister with things you found difficult, such as dressing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, yes, she would help - anything, she wasn't worried what it was, but if - she was needed she was always there you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did she help you to eat and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - no, we were passed that really. Yes, I can't remember her doing that. But - helping us to - get our c
lothes on and things like that she would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would you help the younger one in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, she didn't do very much, she used to run errands sometimes that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well
 - yes, but we used to try and stay up with mother you see after me father died. But we used to - us - two younger ones used to go to bed, and my eldest sister used to stay up with mother, which we used to grumble at because why should she stay up and us 
not you know. But - that's what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, we sort of arranged it - doing for ourselves you know really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Even when you were very young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - yes, in a way, because - you see - well bei
ng three girls it was very different. You know, we - we managed then, times were different really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well my younger sister and I slept together you see and then my mother - eldest sister slept tog
ether. But we had the two - after my father died we had the two beds in one room you see. Because of course she had to let the - other part of the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So you just had the one bedroom then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 We had the one big bedroom, the front bedroom was the big bedroom and then - two big beds in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh we had to have the zinc bath, there was no bathrooms you see then. There is no bathroom - in those houses. We had the bath in front of the fire.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would that be in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes. Brought in from the scullery you see and then my mother used to light the copper - in the kitchen, in the scullery then, with the wood and boil up the water and bring it in in bowls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Is the scullery the same as the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 N
o. Well no, we had a living breakfast room sort of - used to call it the - the living room I think we called that, and then the kitchen was outside where the - the chores were done and the copper was what you light, you know the copper, you light up and g
et the hot water - for everything really, any - of any size, the bathing and - and all the washing she used to do there. No, no bathrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When would you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh about once a week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What day would it be, Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, yes, when it suited her to wash them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
In the middle room, that was - be this side of the kitchen you see. Like a little breakfast room type of thing you know, with - with the kitchen range in, that had to be cleaned with the black}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10566803\charrsid14952291 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 lead you know. Hard going, and clean the flues.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who would have to clean all that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh mother. Yes, of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did one of the sisters help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, because - mother would think that they - she would do it while we were at school you see really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was there any occasion when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. Well we used to be able to sit in there sometimes but that's all, we didn't bother very much about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 The other room was a sort of living room?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes. Yes, more so - of a living room than the other one you know. But as I say we had the bedroom and then we had the living room and the little kitchens, two kitchens you see. That was all after me father died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 And your mother would cook on this range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, everything was done on there. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What time of day would breakfast be eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well, before we went to school of course, yes. About - well what time do you go to school, about half past eight I suppose. Yes
. Mm. 'Cos there was no - we had to walk to school, of course we didn't live far from the school. But if you did live far from the school you still had to walk, there was no transport or anything like you know. Nor no school dinners - you had to bring you
r sandwiches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who would be there, would all your sisters be there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, both my sisters - used to go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That would be the first meal of the day would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Yes. Well then we'd take our sandwiches to school you see. Then come home and have our tea and that would be that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What did you used to have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well, porridge. You know, didn't have bacon and stuff like that like they do now. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What would you drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well tea has been the main beverage hasn't it really always. 'Cos we were - we only had the tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever have anything special on certain days, like a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, I expect - we - no, I don't think the breakfast but we might have had a bit of high tea. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What was that like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What was high tea?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, bit of - jelly and blanc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10566803\charrsid14952291 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 manage and stuff like that I suppose really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When would you have that, what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well our teatime that was you see, she used to cook our dinner you know - of course meat was very much cheaper than it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How often would you have meat during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well couple - three - three times perhaps, you see, soups, she'd buy bones and boil down and make soups for us. We had always plenty of nourishment of course - I wouldn't say it was the best cut but it was always v}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10566803\charrsid14952291 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 ry good. You know, really. In fact -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You say when you were at school you used to have sandwiches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well you see, sometimes we could - we didn't come home, but if we did -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was that right from the word go you didn't come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well, no, sometimes she'd say well there's some dinner, you can come home today, you know, but - sometimes we - play out or do anything you know. We didn't live very far from the school that we - could come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of sandwiches would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh I don't know, anything we could get then. 'Course - as I say the meats were much cheaper, there was - the prob - the problem wasn't meat in those days. I mean the offal was very reasonable. You -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What's that like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Liver, heart - and - you know, what you buy - which is very expensive now, but - well we did - we didn't starve anyway, we were - always -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So you'd have your main meal at night then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well - yes well we had a bit of high tea, we had some - sometimes we'd get a bit of liver fried and onions and stuff. 'Cos well we -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What time of day was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Teatime you know when we got back about five. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would that be the main meal of the day then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, we didn't bother about any more after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You'd have nothing for supper or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. We might have a cup of cocoa you know, cocoa was a big thing in those days. But - we didn't do bad -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have anything special on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
No, I - well she would perhaps - possibly buy a little joint on Sundays. Which wasn't much more expensive really than - the during the week really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What time of day would you eat that, midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh midday yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your mother ever bake her own bread at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, sometimes, but not very often because the baker used to - it was quite handy the shops you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It was a sort of little community was it, Torpoint?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Oh yes. Much smaller than it is now, it's of course terrific over there now with the - Naval you know, the R}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10566803\charrsid14952291 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 liance, Biskard and all that. Lot more people. And houses all built around you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about her own jam, would she do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh she used to make the jams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of jams would she make?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well, if anybody gave her a bit of fruit she'd make a bit of jam, you see. They used to grow currants and strawberries and that all out round and - bring it in you know to sell in Torpoint and if that is - because you see the sugar was c
heap. Then-very very reasonable. In fact it was when I got married, really. Well sugar was two pounds for tuppence ha'penny and now it's - it's two pounds for twenty new pence you see. What's tuppence ha'penny now in the new - decimal? Yes, sixpence is tw
o and half isn't it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about things like bottled fruit or vegetables, did she do anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No. 'Cos that was in the - the last war that the bottled fruit was a big thing. The 1939 war. 'Cos the -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about making pickles, would she do things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, well she'd pickle onions you know. Because we used to all like pickled onions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So it's much more sort of making use of the things around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Rather than nipping round to the shop to buy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes. Oh there wasn't so much of that as there is now. And as you say there's no tinned stuff. So what you didn't have fresh you didn't have at all you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever have dried vegetables and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, there was no such thing 
as that. No. In fact that - that's really only been a big thing this last what - ten years I suppose like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your father and mother ever grow their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well little - yes, but we didn't have a very big garden. No. Bit of grass that's all for us to - have tadpoles out there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 They didn't have any arrangement with a bit of land somewhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no. No, he wasn't home long enough ever to - do a garden, an allotment, anything like that see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 For that reason they wouldn't have any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, we never had anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no poaching, we used to get a rabbit given us sometimes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who would give you the rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh my relatives had a farm and - you know - out the country way that they had a rabbit - or if we went to visit them they might given us one to bring home you know. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How about chickens or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, we didn't get chicken very often. No. We might have had it Christmas time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I don't suppose you remember seeing your mother having less food so the rest of you could have a bit more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, I don't think - I don't know - nothing I know of, but 
of course you never know what mothers - sacrifice do you, or you didn't in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When your father was at home did he have more than anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, he would just have his whack the same as the rest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was any beer brewed for the family at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Is what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Any beer? Home made beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, we were - actually teetotallers. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well, we - we were - rather a tough old lot but - you know, the old camphorated oil for ru
bbing your chest and all this - the old fashioned remedies you know which didn't cost very much you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Your mother wouldn't make her own medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, but - you know, for ear ache, we had earaches all of us, she used to boil the - the - roa
st the center of the onion and put in our ear you know, the old fashioned - very old fashioned, yes. Oh - oh yes. I have recommended it to amount of people who've got little children, and it - you put the - the - center of the onion in the ear hot, and I 
suppose it's the juices that help, I don't know but - it does work. It's a very old fashioned remedy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you allowed to talk during a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well yes, being girls we did - cackle I daresay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 There was no sort of silence rule or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, there was no restrictions, no, in fact you know we weren't really boisterous children - is very different - times then you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 In some families if you talked or anything you were squashed weren't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Oh no, no, we - we just were - well three girls is very different to boys in a family you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, we - it was put in front of us and if we didn't like it t
oo bad. But of course we were pretty easy children to - too, we - we liked whatever she put in front of us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of thing would you have for main meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh - only meat and potatoes and turnips and carrots and - the veg you know, plenty of veg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about if you left some food on the plate uneaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no - but it did - we didn't leave it very often 'cos we - we were glad to get it really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about if there was something on the table you wanted like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, we would say, pass the - this and pass that. Oh yes, we were pretty easy really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about second helpings, could you have them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 W
ell - I suppose if there was any left after it was all doled out we might be able to but - we were pretty - you know, full up after the first lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about holding your knife and fork, were you expected to hold it in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh - well we
 were brought that way really, as little children you know, my mother was very - keen on us being very mannerly you know, as little children really. There was no - rough stuff at all, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about bringing toys or a book to the table, were you allowed to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, we didn't do that. No, we - we had to eat our meal then get down and then - start again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When could you leave the table, at any time or did you have to have permission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, we had to wait and - and ask to be excused. Oh yes, we - couldn't jump down when it suited us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have to wait until everybody had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, they - yes, but most likely they - we were all about the same you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When your father was at a home did all the family sit at the table for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, yes. Yes, at - at the time you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have set positions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well we - we children used to sit always and then he had the head of the table when he was home and mother at the side you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did the children have positions they always went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes. Oh yes, we had our places at the table you know, we knew where we were going to sit before - well I suppose we'd always sat there you see really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It was a sort of habit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where did your younger sister sit before she could feed herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh well high chairs. High chairs. But of course she was six when he died so - she was six years younger than me, that - she always had the - the - chair that was high of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have that before her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh we all had a turn of the high chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did anyone feed you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well, no, but children used to sort of get on with it in those days really. They didn't have these - prepared foods, they had to - no, goodness me no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you remember anything like going mushrooming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh yes, we did used to do that out in the fields. Yes, but you had got to get up very early, we - didn't stick that very long because you had to be out so early. And then you'd find somebody there before you. Y
ou know. Oh you got to get up six o'clock in the morning. To go out and get the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10566803\charrsid14952291  mus}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
hrooms. We did that - several times but - not - we got fed up with that. But mind you - it was nice when you ate them. But you'd find people there long before you were really. Mushrooming. 'Cos they are very nice aren't they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I still go up and get them at Buckfastleigh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you? Do you really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you find your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, yes, well she only had us you see really. Which -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 With your father away so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 He was away so much that - she was really a - a good friend you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did she show a lot of affection for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes, oh she was very fond of us. Because when my father died - we could have gone into a - a s
chool you know, well he was a Freemason you see, but she wouldn't let us go. She said, oh no, I'll keep them home. Although it meant hardship. But she wouldn't let us go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Yes. Yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about your father, was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well, he was but we used to think he was a bit firmer than mother was with us when he came home. Not that he had any occasion to be but he wouldn't have any humbug you know. Like men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Why do you think he was a bit more firm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well, I suppose I - don't know, he - he didn't - I wouldn't say he ever beat us or anything like that but he would make us know when he spoke that it had to be done, where as we would get round mother a bit you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That could easily be because he was a Warrant Officer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes. Well - I suppose so, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well they - we never had any bother, they never had any bothe
r with us three girls you know. We were always out to do what we could for them you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your sisters in any special way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, we - just were - we got on very well all three of us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What would they say if somebody like another child hurt you, would -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh, my older sister would be on them. Yes, she was very good - look after us you know. In fact she's done that all her life actually.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would your parents say retaliate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. We were rather - you know, well - I wouldn't say quiet but - you know, we didn't like any bother you know, fuss of any sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of people do you think your father and mother hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well of course we weren't terribly 
old for them to decide you know, as long as we behaved ourselves and - that sort of thing I should imagine - 'cos we never went far in the evenings you see because there was nowhere to go. And - we were quite happy with our knitting and that and - little 
bits of sewing at home. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did they ever bring you up to consider certain things important in life can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well nothing in particular really, we weren't that old you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about religion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh we always went to church with
 them, and - and we went to Sunday school. And we - well always went to any little does at the church you know. Oh yes, she was rather keen on that side of it, to bring us up that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It would be church would it, not chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Chapel. Methodist chapel. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Anything else perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well no, we used to go as I say to the Band of Hope when we were very little and - sign the pledge against strong drink, that was a very big thing in Torpoint, in years gone by.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was there a lot of drunke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10566803\charrsid14952291 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 ness in that area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well of course the - the men used to pub then a lot more than they do now you see, the pubs were open all day. Mm. Yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would they come round and ask you to sort of sign it or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh it - you - that is the meeting yo
u go and somebody says about the downfalls of drink you see and then as children you think it's terrible and then you sign that you won't take the liquor and all that. But I mean a lot of them used to go for the fun of the thing really, they didn't even k
now what they were signing. But - yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well that - that we never had in the home. No. We wouldn't have done that. I don't think we were ever been brought - we had that ever - had occasion to hear that in our home. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about if grown ups were talking, were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well we didn't - because we didn't think that would be very popular anyway. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What would happen if you did something your mother or father disapproved to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh w
ell, they would be very hurt, we - they never - we never had a hiding of any description but - they would say, well now, we never thought you'd do that, you know, sort of - thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of things would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, I don't know what we would
 do but if we did do anything that we shouldn't do they'd say, well we didn't think you'd have done that. You know? But - as I say really, being six, twelve and fourteen there wasn't much - we hadn't got to the stage when we would be doing something very 
m
uch that they didn't like you see really. Because we spent most of our time in the home. When we came home from school we didn't - we might have played out in the back lane with hoops and - things like that but that's about all. Yes, yes, whip along the -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You wouldn't be sent to a little room or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No, we - we weren't a bit - as I say I think it's the boys that are little bit turks really when they're that age aren't they?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would you say that you received the ideas you
 had about how to behave from both your parents or would your mother play a more important part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well - mother really, because he would let - her be - the head of the house because he wasn't there so often you see, so whatever she said - he thought was right you see for us. Especially being girls you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I suppose girls sort of learn more from their mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well I think so really, yes, yes. Yes, I - I think the mother's really the one. Where there's - daughters really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well we might have got a little bit of extra tea, I - I don't think - I don't remember having any present - big presents ever. Well of course we - we didn't - have the income for it and - and of course 
birthdays weren't considered like they are today. You know, birthdays there's big parties and all sorts now aren't there? I don't think we ever had a party as kids. We used to go to Sunday school parties that's about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of presents did you say you received?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well we wouldn't - wouldn't get very much, we might have a pair of gloves that we knew that we had to have you know. It wouldn't be anything that - outstanding that's for certain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You wouldn't have anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about Christmas Day, would anything special happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well we used to go to an aunt's always on Christmas Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where did she live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well not too far away from us but we used to - go there and have the
 day and play snap and ludo and - of course there was nothing - we'd play the piano a little bit and - but that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would you have present or anything on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, we didn't bother about that, I don't think we ever had any presents. I don't remember having any anyway?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Anything special to eat, you say you had rabbit sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well - yes, but I think we used to go to this - the aunt of ours and she used to have a - you know, bird of some sort. Well we used to have a nice day there always on Christmas Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have any musical instruments in your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Only the - well we had a piano. Yes, 'cos we learned the piano, all three of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You had special tuition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, we did then, but when my father died I had 
to pack up because it was - she couldn't afford - us all to go you see. So previous to that my sister had given over and then - came to that I couldn't - go, I couldn't learn any more. And so I've never kept it up really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You gave it up in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well yes, I didn't - well of course if you don't practice you don't - you can't learn you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How about your sister, she was older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well she could play, she - she - yes, well she didn't - she dropped it after a while, yes. Yes, no
ne of us have - really carried on with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did anyone sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. I expect we thought we did anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You didn't have sort of family sing-songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well now sometimes we used to go to church on Sunday nights you see and bring home a f
ew - girls or - you know, and sing around the piano, my mother used to play the hymns. And - that's all we used to do you see, might have had a cup of tea before they went home but - they didn't get very much you know. But it was somewhere for 'em to go y
ou see. After church, 'cos the - well there was nothing else for us to do and they used to come home with us and used to have a sing-song before they went home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You didn't ever make music around the piano with your father and mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, well no, he - no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I don't think so. No. We made our own amusements, the three of us you see really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You were lucky really being quite close to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, we were close to each other, in - i
n age you see that we sort of - well my - especially my older sister and I, were very close, have been up to now when she died last year - two years ago. Because - my other - the one six years old, we never wanted you see, to play with us because she was 
too young. She was the odd one out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh well we used to get books I suppose you know from school and - there was no such thing as library of course. Might have got a book given us. I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your parents have any books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
No, no, they didn't - they didn't read a - very much. Well in fact he - we were always having - you know, chatting when he was at home, but when me mother you see, we - she was doing a bit of sewing and that, she didn't read very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Didn't read the newspapers or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes, she used to have the Sunday Companion always, once a week, and she used to read that. And give it to a neighbour you know in those days that's what used to happen. Pass it round you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So what kind of house was it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh terraced. Terraced house yes. You know. What they call 'em town house now isn't it, don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about magazines, would she have any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was the Sunday Companion the local paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
No, it was a - it's a paper - well a weekly you know like ordinary weeklies, but I - I think - I expect that would be about a penny. You know, it wasn't very - she wouldn't have had it if it had been costing very much you see anyway. But she always
 had her Sunday Companion and she used to sit down Sunday afternoon and read it. And then pass it on you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would you read it as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well no, I don't think we did. We used to go to Sunday school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That would be in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That's the afternoon - morning and afternoon we used to go. Then - in the evening we used to go to chapel with her you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did she just go that once in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, she used to go once. She didn't go in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your father or mother ever read anything aloud to you, like stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I don't think they did really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you ever remember something like a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I remember me father's funeral, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who came to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well all the
 relatives you know. Yes, I do remember that, I was twelve you see. And I remember him being ill for three months before he died. In the house. And - of course when he died his - he was - buried from the house, there was no chapel of repose or anything li
ke that, the corpses were in the house until the burial you see. And - that's the only one I remember. In those days of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would you sort of have mourning clothes and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Yes. We had little - black and white frocks and - black hats and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where would you get them from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well - somebody - made them up for us you know. Of course mourning was rather a big thing in those days. Black clothes - you know, mm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 They had a custom round our way of closing the curtains.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, oh the blinds down. While they died, until the funeral, 'til after the funeral, always the blinds down. Everywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What happened after the funeral?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well then they came back from the funeral and pulled up the blinds you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you ever taken out to visit neighbours when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I don't think we'd do much of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - we had an aunt, that's all, that lived in our vicinity. My mother only had one sister you see. And she was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When you had the funeral where would they come from then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh she was there, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were there many people at the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - one or two, you know, near relatives really. And friends, you know, neighbours and that but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who would you go out to visit relations with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh only my aunt. She was the only - my mother's only sister. And we used to go there on occasions to know if she wanted any shopping done and things like that. But - this visiting was never very - well we never did a lot of that really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever go out shopping or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh we used to do the errands for our mother that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You didn't ever go out on sort of a Saturday morning spree or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever go out shopping with your mother or was it just for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well - no, she didn't go out very much really. She'd take us for walks and sometimes. But of course there was nothing - no buses or anything like that. You'd go for a walk and that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you remember just going out for a walk with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well, he would take us out - go up in the fields with a ball and things like that, that's all. We didn't do a lot really in our young days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you remember any outings at all with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh we on - we used to go the Sunday school treat. And we used to all go in wagonettes you know to a field - away out in the country, and - take our mugs - for our cup of tea you see. That's all. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who would go with you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh they - all the mothers of the children. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Once a year was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It would be around here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh it didn't go very far, only - where a horse - and trap could take you you know, not - no cars you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever go any other holidays with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, never had a holiday nowhere those days, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you remember any Bank Holidays, I suppose that wouldn't apply really would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, we didn't go very far, we used to walk to the Whitesa
nds which was six miles out. That's the seaside. You know, at the other side of Porpoint. Six miles out on the cliff there. We used to walk there. And we used to stop half way and have a penny glass of milk in the farm. That's about all we ever did. Took 
our - bit of eats I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would there be any special way you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
No, I don't think we did very much, no. Saturday was as good as any other day you know. Ours was a very really - well - I suppose- we didn't think it was monotonous in those days, but - anybody today would wonder how you survived really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It's walking and doing bits round the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. That's all - that's all you did in those days you see. Well there was nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 But some days you say you'd go to the Sunday school twice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes, twice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of things would you do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well, only be talks or - you know, I mean - messages from the Bible and things like that. They didn't have any sand trays and stuff like they d
o now to entertain the children. Oh no, we just went to school, and - as we got older we went into the choir and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you remember anything like a choir outing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh - on - yes, yes, well I was older then you see. But of course you
 don't - you don't go in the choir until you're about fourteen, fifteen you see. So that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That would be after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes. Yes. Oh they did have some - little outings then, but we used to go by train, the only way to go anywher
e. There was no coaches you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Whereabouts would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well, out on the moors. You know, out to Shaw. And you wouldn't know that but it's a - it used to be a small train that take you to the moors. Then you had to come from Torpoint onto 
the ferry, go up to Devonport station and catch the train out, and the same back. No - trams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you get paid for doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. Oh no, you got to pay to go. Yes. Not a lot you know in those days. We'd pay our own train fare, that was all it was really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How long were you in the choir for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh until I got married I think. Six years, five years, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were both your other sisters in the choir as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. I don't think the little one was, 'cos she - never could carry a tune. I
n fact - her - after - well after five years you see, after I left - well no it wasn't while I - before I left, it was before I left that - my mother married - again, and - of course our home life was very different then - again, but then I was - it was i
n 1914 - my mother married, and - I got married in 1919 so I wasn't home very long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you sort of have different clothes to wear on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What would that consist of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, nothing startling but something different to what we wore to school. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You wouldn't have school uniform I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no such thing as that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you allowed to play games or anything on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. And we weren't allowed to do our sewing on a Sunday. Nor - anything - that could be done on a Saturday was done - to ease off Sunday.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What could you do on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh nothing. No. And if you had a button off your shirt - it would remain off, because - mother wouldn't sew it on Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was it your mother or your father who said that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well mother most so because he was - broadened his outlook being in the Navy and going abroad and all that you see. But mother was very - well like we all were in those days, a little bit the strait and narrow you know 
really. But - we're none the worse for that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did both your mother and father go to chapel or just your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well he did when he was home, yes, with her. But she was the one, she - she would go you know always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You say it was Methodist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It is Methodist, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 She'd go once on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Once a day. Once a Sunday. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were there any other activities organized by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You say the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well that was all. Yes, they didn't do anything else. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 The sort of temperance club, was the the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well that is the Band of Hope, the temperance - the - the temperance people ran it actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you a member?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh go along to the meetings, all - all the kids around used to g
o. You see, oh it was a - quite an affair that, we used to enjoy that. Not that we did anything. But it - it - in those days it was very very - sparse, anything other than home life really. There was nothing to do, no - no act - nothing for children you s
ee much that - but to play out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was grace ever said at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who would say that, your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, and if - well either one of us you know, she would say, well say your grace then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did father say it when he was home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, he didn't, he - listened to us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you taught to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes? We always said our prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of prayers would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, just the little prayers you know, God bless mother and father and - make us good girls and all this sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
No. No. No, that was a bit before my time, because my - I know my mother used to say her father used to have family prayers, but it never came - in our time, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You say you didn't have much leisure activities before leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 We hadn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You can't remember anything like fairs or circuses?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - we might have had a little circus come to the town, but - nothing very - nothing at all really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you remember going to the circus at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well - it was really more sideshows, you know, not animals or anything like that. And the girl used to sing done up in spangles which we thought was beautiful you see. And - but as I say, it wasn't
 a circus, because - there wasn't a big enough place over to Torpoint to have any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did the fairs ever come round, traveling fairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No, not in my young days, not my very young days. They had - oh I don't think they did, they - they might have 
come - the traveling fairs but not very often. There's not enough people there to - justify them coming you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How small a place was Torpoint?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh it wasn't very big. I can't re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid870449\charrsid14952291 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 ll}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid870449\charrsid14952291 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291  you the population off hand but - but it was quite a - a small 
place, 'cos they've built - right out around now, there's - the - the - it's only the center you see really that we used to know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who did you play with when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh only me -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was it mainly your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well the - the kids next door that's all you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were they girls or boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well some of each. We did - we didn't do very much anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were they your age group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. About ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where about would you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh, in the back gardens. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of things would you play, would you play ball games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well ball games mostly, you know. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Making dolls houses and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes - well, no, trying to sew doll's clothes on and tat if we'd had dolls given us, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you get many dolls in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, yes, you - girls had dolls you know. But of course nothing in comparison to what they are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You wouldn't have things like nurse's outfits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, we'd be lucky. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well they don't get dirty really, we used to wear pinafores you know, of course they never do that now. But - we always had the - the - to keep the frock clean we wore pinafores you see. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would you play in other people's homes, you say you didn't go visiting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, we didn't. No, we didn't go out very much in other people's houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You'd get on OK with the neighbours, it was a friendly street was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, they were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 There are some districts where nobody ever spoke.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, they - they are all schoolchildren that used to live there you see. More or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You often hear that it was much friendlier in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Everybody knew everybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well they did know everybo
dy else but - people - when they - they'd done their shopping and that they went into their own homes. I don't think people had enough money to entertain you see that they just kept themselves - with the family life you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you ever a member of any youth organi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5178718\charrsid14952291 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 ations?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No, I don't think there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 There wasn't a YHWCA or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh no, no. No, not in Torpoint anyway. No, I don't think there was actually - that is really not - not - for - sp far back as my time. Because this is new this YWCA and YMCA isn't it really. It was a wartime thing wasn't it? Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you allowed to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, yes, they didn't worry too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did they ever say you mustn't play with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well no, I - they were all much the same type as ourselves that lived around us you see. You know, just the - ordinary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have any hobbies in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I don't think we did really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You did sewing you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That's about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about collecting things, did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Stamps or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, no stamp collecting in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Now about gardening, did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. None of us liked gardening. I think we had grass and then - som
ebody used to have to push the mower, if they were un - lucky, I don't know, I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever have any pets around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, we didn't, I - well we had a cat, that's all. But we were rather keen on - going to a pond and ge
tting some tadpoles and then we had a little pond in the garden and let 'em come to frogs you know, then they were hopping all over the place.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have a pond in the garden then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well we used to have a bowl you see and - and sink it in the garden and - we had lots of fun with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did they actually get into frogs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, yes, they did, and then they climbed out over and off - off they went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well I don't know where they went. I expect somebody else had 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh - oh not until we were - my mother married again. And then he - my step-father gave us a bike each then. And we were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When did she remarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 In 1914. Yes. But - of course we were made then. When he b
ought us a bike each. I don't mean to say he wanted to buy his popularity because - he - we knew him all our lives. We used to call him uncle. And - his first wife was a great friend of my mother's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 He lived nearby did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, he lived quite near us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What did he do for a living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 He was a Naval man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was he a Warrant Officer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Actually he was a Lieutenant when she married him. But - he lived 'til he was ninety. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Quite recent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, my - yes, ten years he's been - off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did the fact that she remarried sort of ease the poverty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh yes, yes, that made a big difference to us, because we went to live in his house you see. Which wasn't very far away. Yes, it's made a difference to us all really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was it a similar kind of house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, it was a terraced house, but it was a big - you know, it was a - a bigger house than ours actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How many rooms did it have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, it might have had the seven rooms but we had the seven rooms, and he had a bat
hroom in his house. Yes, so he was one of the clean ones. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So it was quite a big event?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well it was a good thing for my mother when she married again, and for us really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I suppose he'd be involved in the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, yes,
 he was at Dunkirk. In the first war, no, not - no - the - yes, the first world war isn't it? Dunkirk? I don't mean this - I don't mean this - this evacuation of Dunkirk. He was over there - oh no, it was the first world war he was in. Yes. And - they use
d to run the - he - he used - he was based at Immingham in the North of England and I think they - he used to oversee boats that were going across to France, as much as I can remember of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about the husband and wife who moved into your flat after your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well then they went and bought their own house. Then they wanted to go out - the went out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of work did he do, the tenant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, he - oh I think he was in the dockyard. Oh yes. But he - he - was quite willing
 to go. And he went and bought his own place and - and so my mother sold that house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So you got your bicycles anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 We got our bicycles. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How old would you be then, you'd be about seventeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, about that. Yes, about seventeen I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever go fishing or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, no, never - no, no, only our tapoles, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about any sports, did you go in to any sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No, we didn't do that. I don't think much sport was - on
ly racing at the tea parties and things like that you know. You know, running the hundred yards and stuff, you know, and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were there any things like cinemas at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 There was no cinema. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Nothing at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Why do you think that was, because quite a lot of places have music halls and things don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh well, I don't think that Torpoint would have done anything with it. I don't think - anybody would venture it really. Well, eventually - just after I - wel
l when I was - about to move I think it was, a - a man - opened up a - place there but it didn't go down very well. Because I think if people wanted to have a change they'd come to Plymouth. You only had to come on the - the - water you see, quarter of an
 hour ferry, and you were - in Devonport.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever go into Plymouth for any of these things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
No, I never did. No. Well we didn't go 'cos you see - well we were - getting on and we knew some boys over to Torpoint that we used to go out around with and - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of things would you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, then I mean - walks, yes. Had to be in by nine. None of your midnight oil with us. Oh no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you ever given any pocket money while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. But if we wanted a penny for anything we'd have to ask you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 They'd give it to you if it was possible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes, she - she would give us a -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, when we felt that we wanted to buy something we'd ask her you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of thing would you buy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well a few sweets you see. Yes. Oh here's my -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you remember if your father ever took any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No he didn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you remember whether he ever voted in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well I expect he would have done by proxy you see. Because he - it would have gone to the ship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You'd no idea what he voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I wouldn't know that. Not now anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you think your father ever felt under any pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - I - I can't say that, I don't know really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You get these ideas sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, but he - it - it was never brought up in the home, un - unless - with me mother I wouldn't know that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So your father wasn't a member of any political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How did the parents spend their time when they weren't doing their work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, they used to sit in the garden, they didn't do very much really when you - 'cos he didn't get a lot of leave you know. N
o. I don't remember them - ever gadding around anywhere anyway. He used to go and visit his parents and that you know, which lived in Torpoint. Used to do the regular there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your mother have any interests outside the home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No,
 only the church. Yes. She - she used to go to a sewing class, you know, belonging to the church, but - she used to find that her home, you know, was plenty to do}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 They didn't have any sort of whist drives and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, no, she - no, there was nothing like that - no, s don't think whist - came into it, not in those days anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 She would never go out when your father was away at sea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. Oh no, no. It - it's rather an uneventful life you see for us really. But of course that was the - the times you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How often in the year would your father be on leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh well - it all depends what job he had you see, he was abroad you see for a while, and then he came home and he had a ship in the home fleet, which used to come in every three months, for a fortnight, and - that sort of thing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So he'd have about what, a month or so in the year with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, a year, that's about all. And you see if - if his ship was in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I suppose you can't remember him all that much if he was only home once in a while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your father, when he was home from sea, attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 He was teetotal as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, he wasn't a staunch teetotaler, but we never had it in the home. In
 fact he didn't worry too much but I think he used to - go ashore like and have a drink, you know, but not in - when he was home he was only too glad to be in you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your father take part in any sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would he go to any of the horse races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. Well there wasn't a thing on by that way you see anyway, whether he did it when he was abroad I don't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did he belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No. Their - their salaries weren't all that that t
hey could save very much, by the time they paid their way - you know, that was about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about something like a Frie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 dly Society maybe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. I don't think so. He was a Freemason, but then we didn't ever hear anything much about that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 He didn't sort of put in money for sickness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, not that I know of you see what happened there but - with them I wouldn't know you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did anyone outside of the home ever help - your mother look after the house or the family when your father was away at sea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
No, because she could never go - I mean if his ship put into port some - anywhere, she couldn't afford to go. To him. So we didn't have to ; anybody to look after us you see. Because - she was always at home with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever have relatives, was she ever sick at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well no, she wasn't really. Well if so my other sister you see would have been able to - if she wanted to stay, but she never - I don't remember her ever being ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You didn't have to call in relatives or anything to help look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you remember anything of when your younger sister was born? Can you remember what happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, 'cos I was only - six you see, no, I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You say you only had your mother's sister living close?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well she lived quite near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about your father's side of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, there was, but - they - they - my father used to visit. But - my mother, she - visit on occasions but - they had their own 
interests really. They were quite all right you know but - and mother didn't worry too much.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So you only saw this aunt really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well she was the main one, me mother's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 She was the one you went to stay with at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. No, t
he l it was another - well we used to call her aunt but she wasn't any relation to us, the Christmas one really. She was a - an - oh just a very old friend of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was your father home very often at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - on occasions but he us
ed to go as well. If he was home, but - more than likely - when he was abroad a good bit, he - he wasn't at Christmas you see and sometimes he'd have a Christmas leave and some - a New Year leave you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I suppose when your mother remarried your way of life wouldn't change all that much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Not a lot. Not a lot, because - it was the same kind of life, it's Torpoint again you see. Which is always - didn't alter very much over there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your parents have many friends, did your father bring many friends back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
No, he didn't. No. They - you see, they were usually Devonport ships that they all - most of the men belonged to Devonport you see, and they had their own homes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What does a Warrant Officer do anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well now I can't tell you 
that now. I don't know. He was in charge of - a series of carpenters I think because his - his trade was carpentry. You see, and - when they - they oversee the carpenter - the ships - the mending of the woodwork I should imagine. But of course that was re
ally a long way back for me that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your father and mother have the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Or did your mother perhaps have friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, no, we were all sort of - you see, in - in a place - a small place you - you - every
body knows everybody. So you - see them around and about the shops and - various you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were friends ever invited into the home, your home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. Well the - the - they didn't seem to wa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 t to come anyway, each had their own interest in their own
 home, in their own families and - that's it - it you know. See and - you see, after all 19 - before 1914 it was a very different world to what it is today. And very different to what it was in the last war really. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 They wouldn't be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No. And there was no cafes or anything like that in Torpoint you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would there be any special days or occasions when they might pop round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No, I - I think they were all pleased to be - not living their own lives really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 If they did come round there'd be no invitations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, they just drop in on the way you know and - go again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That was sort of friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Well - just - just people that we knew around you know, chapel where we belonged.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever have any people come back after chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well no - little children used to sometimes with us, but - not women didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Your parents wouldn't go out much to visit friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well no, they didn't rea
lly. In fact, they didn't do a lot of visiting in those days. People were quite happy in their own homes. You know, they didn't look for other company really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 We often hear that people in those days made their own amusements, what would you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well I don't know what they could have done, just - played cards and - not cards even - not as cards as we know it, you know, just the little simple snap cards and - happy families and - cards you know and - the ludo -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 This was mainly the children wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well my - my mother used to sit and do the sewing or knitting or anything you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You hear about society being divided into different social classes and groups.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I wouldn't say that over there. No. I think there wasn't very 
- very - I wouldn't say there were rich people around. The business people that's all, you know the shop keepers. Well they - just made a living I suppose. But there was no class you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 There was no sort of gentry living there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no - Sir Ge
n - the - General - Sir Polcaroe, he lived at Anthony, well he was - a General in the Army but he would be the only - what I would call - the gentry then you see, he put up - for - the Conservatives - you know, in the - very young days, when we used to - 
h
ear of them, you know - having meetings, you know, political meetings, but then that didn't mean much to me. But I know Sir Reginald used to be - that put up for the Conservatives. And Isaac Foot. That would be - a bit later though than what you're asking
 me. As the Liberal candidate, that was - that would be late - yes, because - it - you're - you're - much a - before that you see really. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So you sort of really think that in those days it was mainly sort of the Naval families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That's all. And the shopkeepers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well - there was the vicar of the church - he lived in a big house quite near us, and of course the Methodist minister he - they come for four years and go, they - move along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What did you think of them as?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well yes, they would be looked up to rather. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What would you think of yourself, your family as being in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, we - oh we would think that we were - you know, quite on a par with - most people there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would you be the same as the shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, yes, and - Naval Officers were rather - thought of as - a little bit above the average you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of people belonged to the same group, just the Naval Officers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well it was the Naval people mostly. Yes. Or - or -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would you think of it as being middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes. Yes. Yes, I would - but I wouldn't say there - well we had a couple of solicitors lived in our road, but they didn't seem to be any better than what we were, you know, they'd just have their little offices and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about the workings classes, where would they live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well they - they would have been - yes, but - they lived more - down by the water way you know, they were dockyard people more. Dockyard labourers and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you on a hill or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well we lived more at the top of the town anyway you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was that the top end of the town with the better houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where the better people - yes, the better - houses were really. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you remember being brought to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, we were a friendly people. I think most of 'em were really. You know, the business people were very - very sociable and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you ever told to curtsey to anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No, there was nothing like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was there anyone you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No, we - I don't think we did. I - I think - perhaps lots of people would call the doctor sir but - we never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who were considered the most important people in Torpoint at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well I suppose the councillors were. Who - I don't know - who they would be but - the - the local council people, you know, they're elected by the people. To - look after them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Is it a village or a town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well it's a town really, supposed to be, but I don't - it had a council and - chairman of the council and that you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It wouldn't be sort of like you get the towns with local owners of the mills?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well there was n
othing like that at Torpoint, you see, no - no - I think the dockyard and the Navy took up all the - most of the - and - they'd be away, 'cos the dockyard people were the ones that - used to sort of - be - looking after the - ratepayers association and th
ings like that really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about solicitors and doctors, would you think they were sort of important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, I think they were the - little bit a cut above - most people over there I should imagine. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about shopkeepers, who did they go around with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well no, they had their own - way of living really you know. 'Cos the shops used to be open 'til very late at night that they didn't have very much time. Because shops were always open you know. I don't know that they opened Sundays. 
They - they didn't really I don't think. But - normally you know they were - eight in the morning 'til eight at night and - or later. Because they were mostly shop - owner shops you see. So that a - every pound counted then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were they sort of easy to get on with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, well they were out for custom you see, there was no - multiple shop then. Each was for their own so it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever come into contact with teachers and farmers and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well no, only the teachers at the schools you see. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were they considered well to do in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh no, they weren't. No, because - I suppose they were college trained, a few of them, but - it wasn't important that you had to be - college trained to be a teacher then. You know, they were - well un - like un}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
certificated you see but they taught and they we - we kids got on just as well - as some of the - 'cos I suppose the - head of departments would have to have gone to college wouldn't they? But - as I say - teaching was
n't what it is today you know in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What were the farms like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes. Well they used to do - I think - I don't know whether they used to give a lot, farmers have never been - had a name for being very generous have they really. No. 'Cos the
 - we used to have a woman that came in a pony and trap with the butter and eggs once a week. That was from a - smallholding I suppose, and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would she sell it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. The butter and the eggs and a bit of vegetable and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of people would you say went to the church, would there be a difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, all just like ourselves you know. Friendly sort you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Sometimes the gentry go to the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, they don't, no, there wasn't anybody that wen
t to the chapel that I went that was anybody - of note anyway, so - but there's a little village outside Torpoint that - that the - well - not the royalty - used to stay with this General, you know, well they used to a - they used to attend Anthony church
, Maryfield church it's called, but they went there if there was any - that was about two miles out of Torpoint.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was there a church in Torpoint itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, there is a church of England, and a Catholic. There wasn't in my day but there is a Cathol
ic church now over there, but - when I was a child there was only the Methodist - the Congregational and the Church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who would go to the churches, would anyone go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well anybody could go where they liked you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 There wasn't any sort of division?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, no, in fact if you wanted any help I think they would all turn in you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Would you say, can you remember whether all the people in the working class had the same standard of living, the ones that lived at the bottom end of the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, no. No, I - I don't know the people there but - well they were really the working class in a way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you remember much poverty around at that time? Real poverty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - yes, if they didn't have the income coming in - there was no help you know. In any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What was it like in Torpoint for employment, was there regular employment?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, but - not a terrible lot you know outside the dockyard I don't think. Road sweep - I don't if they had road}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 sweepers in those days, I don't remember. But a person who's sal - their wages were poor weren't they in those days anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So none of their little kids or anything to touch their hat when you walked by or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your mother and father have the same attitudes to different classes do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, they were very - friendly you know with everybody. We did - we didn't feel there was very many people better than ourselves. No.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever feel there was anybody below you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - I - we wouldn't really make any - difference with people that weren't - well I used to have a woman that used to c}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 llect my washing, well she only had her bit of washing money and mangling money, but I used to be as friendly with her, poor old dear
 you know, as - anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291 This is aft}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 er you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes. Yes. Well in 1919. But - my mother used to - when my father's time, she had a woman that used to come to do washing, you know, shilling an hour or something like that. She used to come and light the copper and get on with the washing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 This is when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes. Yes, before my father died. And he died in 1910. But I remember old - mother - granny Searle we used to call her, she used to come every Monday and do the washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That would be for the whole week would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh yes. Yes. But she'd do the lot, she would be washing five o'clock in the evening, you know, from the morning. You know, take her time, because she would be elderly you see. But that was her means of - support.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 She used to go around all the families doing some?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, different - different people you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was this the norm?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh that was the normal if you could afford to pay her you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever have anybody else come in to do any other choeres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
No. No, my mother used to - only do the washing, have her to do the washing, when my father was alive. 'Course after my father died she had to do it herself you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 None of you girls did the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you think your mother saw herself belonging to a particular social class, was she conscious of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh no, well her father was a builder in Torpoint, he didn't do it exceptionally well but - he took the drink a while and - and trade, all they had went. S
o that - made her a little bit - yes, more keen on the temperance - she - she upheld that too 'til the day she died, she didn't have no - time for the drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you drink at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I don't. No. I've always felt - well I never did and I wouldn't take it up now anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Have you got any strict views on in yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh no. I don't drink, but I - I'm not worried about other people if they do and I'm quite happy - I mean if they like a drink, well well and good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I think the period when it was a danger is passing now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh my - there have been downfalls with it you know, in the young days. Well they didn't have the only to do it with and when they did - when the drink - was - when the money was gone that way it wasn't in the home you see. That was the trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 But you say this happened more amongst the working class folks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, I do think that because I think the men would go out to the pubs - for a change you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you think it was possible at this time to move from one class group to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, I don't think so. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Say somebody like your mother's father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well he was in a very good way. You know, he built all the - little terraces that when he retired - or before he retired he drank, oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What would he be regarded as then, would he still be regarded the same class group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes, but I know, they - they don't want you when you haven't got the money. My mother used to say that, she said, he had many friends when he had money but - after that nobody knew him when he lost his money you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would he be regarded as working class then or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well he was retired you see, yes, yes. And he went away - went to live with some relatives well then he came back, of course - he had nothing but - his old age pension or what - yes, ten bob a week they used to give 'em then didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You don't think your mother was particularly conscious of class and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No. Well it had died out before my time more or less you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you remember anyone around the area being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, we didn't really have that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were some families thought of as rough at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, I don't know that really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You can't remember so}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291 rt of distinctions between craft}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 smen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I - I'm afraid I don't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you ever remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well, they used to - walk around then. I think we had about two policemen
 in Torpoint. It wasn't a - 'cos there wasn't the crime - no such thing as that there in those days that there is today. I don't think anybody had anything to steal anyway, you know, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were they around your area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well up one street and down the other you know. Not very frequent I don't think. I don't remember seeing much policemen ever.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You never recall being told by your mum when you were naughty I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, no. No, no. Well no, not in - in our home, it w
as very - you know - in fact, there wasn't much really that - happened in - in - our home, much really. You know. Me as a small girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You never got any idea of how the policemen treated other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I don't really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was your home a rented home or did your father own it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh it was owners. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What happened when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh well then she - had - she let it, you see, to pay the mortgage that she had on it. Until she married again see. She - she sold the house then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you remember feeling that you had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Before your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. No, not before me father died, but the years between - him dying and - her marrying again was a bit sticky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What did you think about it at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well we didn't really - realize that it was like it because she kept - you know, most of it away from us, it was - you know, she wasn't very happy like as well. But anyway we struggled through you know. It was only five years anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you say a little bit more about what difference it made to the family when your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well - of course his - his - pen - his sal - his - wages or salary or whatever it was - stopped, and then her pension was made nine shillings a week. That's what she had coming in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You'd have left school, no you'd still be at school would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
I left school. I didn't leave school but I was going to a - a school in Plymouth which I had to leave and go back to the - town school. Because sh
e couldn't pay the fees you see. We - my sister and I, all three of us came over to Plymouth to school. From Torpoint. We weren't the only ones you know, quite a - few girls come over, but then when my father died you see - we had to leave the school and 
go back to the school that was - belonging to the council I suppose over there wouldn't it be. Where you didn't have to pay anything you see. I was there from twelve 'til - fifteen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 At the town school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 At - yes, at the town school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That was non-fee paying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It wasn't fee paying, but I went to - Plymouth to school when I was seven. Until - my father died when I was twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Whereabouts in Plymouth was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Still the Admiral - still the Admiral school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Is that just across the river?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, and - and - not very far this side of the water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you ever given lessons by one of your parents before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, no, we went to school when we were five you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did this apply to all three sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about the oldest sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well she went to the same school as me. And she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about your young sister, did she have to come back to town council school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well she wasn't going to school, she was much as ever going to s
chool was - so she was - she - she went to a - a private school in Plymouth, but she was only - six you see when - my mother married again. So when my father died - now what happened now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 She'd be six wouldn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, she was six. Yes, well she went to Plymouth school when she was six or seven. She never went to the - ordinary school anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You'd be five when you first went to school you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well we - we - had to go at five didn't we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would you go every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, no, every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What time of day would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well nine 'til four isn't it. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You say you didn't come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 We used to nip home to dinner - if we wanted to you know, but - most times I think we went home to dinner but failing that we t
ook a few sandwiches. But - we didn't live terribly far away from the school. But however far we'd lived we'd had to walk it, anyway, there was no such thing as transport.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How much a year was it, the fees for the school, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well I w
ouldn't know. I forget. But the - the town school we didn't pay at all, but when we came over to Stoke Daverall school in Plymouth - there was a fee then. And we were both going there, because - my youngest sister hadn't - well she'd never started school.
 And then she came over to the same school as us but then my mother was in different circumstances then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was it a mixed school or just a girls school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Girls school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Now how long did it take you to get to school, was it very long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
No, well we used to catch a ferry you see, quart - every quarter of an hour the ferry, and then it was about a quarter of an hour to walk when we got over to Devonport side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So you'd have to leave about eight o' clock time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh we used to catch the - quarter past eight ferry I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who would go with you, your elder sister?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. And a couple of - girls from Torpoint used to go as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did all the girls from your area go to this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well several of them, yes. It was - it 
was - felt that you were having that little bit better education really. It wasn't a mixed school anyway you see and - it was a - the town school's a mixed school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What did you think of the difference between the two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well we liked the girls school. We were at a loss when we were taken away and back to town school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What was the standard like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh very nice indeed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of things were different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well they did gymnasium things like that that we didn't do, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 In the new - in the better - in this girls school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 In the girls school you did gym?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. And - uniform and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You did have a uniform in that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 In there. Well - not perhaps so much a uniform but for gymnasium and for the different - we had to have the - the rig you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about more sort of academic things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Well I think - quite nice school really. But - of course it didn't last all that long really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you do English?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Ye
s? Well you did things like that you see. But with a - being a mixed school you sort of parted up for sewing and - you know, it was different altogether really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of subjects would you do at the girls school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh the girls - oh well - all the subjects more or less you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 History and geography?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes. Yes. Yes. No we didn't do music. But as I say, the - gymnastics and they had a gymnasium in the school which they didn't have at the Torpoint school you see. In fact it was a very nice few years there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How many girls were at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh, I don't know I'm sure. It's a big school you know. Because it took in the Plymouth children as well. Plymouth girls you see. But - of course as I say I - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you think that they sort of looked after you better in the girls school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well - yes, more interested in - in - and the teachers were - college trained teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What was the kind of school in Torpoint?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well just the ordinary board school sort of what they us
ed to call, we - I think we used to take a penny a week or something like that. In those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you come home for your meal when you were at the town school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. Well that was the Torpoint school you mean? No, well no that - we used to nip hom
e then really to dinners you know. But of course we didn't - when we came to Plymouth to school we had to bring our sandwiches, or buy a pasty at the shop or something like that. No school meals you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What did you think about the teachers in the first school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well there was men as well as women you see. Well they were all right I suppose really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You say that the female teachers only in the girls school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How did you get on with those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh very nicely indeed. Very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of thing would they look for in girls?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, they were always very nice and they were kind - and if you couldn't grasp it they - they - you know - helped you out you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did they expect things like manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well - I think that had you - fallen over there they would have been - given you a talking to you know. Yes. Oh yes, they were very ladylike - teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you remember whether they expected you to be punctual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh - oh yes, they - they wouldn't 
have any rough stuff. Well of course they didn't get it, it was all girls you know, and they were pretty nice family girls really. Yes. And the - the headmistress was a perfect lady. You know, she - was. Very pshly dressed and she was in her office, you -
 she used to walk around and - and just have a look at the classes but she never taught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was it very strict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well they wouldn't have any nonsense you know. They expected you to behave like - young ladies really in a way, and I think most of them -
 well they were pretty good really, what I could -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of thing would the girls do when they left the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well, they would go on for teaching - you know, they stayed on, of course I left. And - I - I didn't want to go on to - to be a
 teacher or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were there any boarding facilities at this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, they didn't board anybody, no, it was only a day school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What would happen if you did something the teachers disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well you'd have to go
 in and be talked to by the head. Yes. If it was any - I never was in there but I would imagine if you were - you know, anything did happen and you were sent in there for - it wouldn't be - you wouldn't ve very happy about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You wouldn't get the stick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, there was no stick, but I think - it hurts more when you're talked to really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about when you went to the town school, did you notice much of a change in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, well they were a different type of - children, was boys on
e side and girls the other and - throwing paper about and - the headmaster was - very strict there though, he used to give the boys the cane and all that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I suppose this would be quite a shock to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well it did - it was a shock when we went back there. Yes, we didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did people treat you any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, but they didn't have much to say to us because we didn't - we'd been away five years you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were boys and girls from your neighbourhood at the town school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well, yes, but they - not so much - well we got on all right there really I suppose, but we weren't there very long you see, when we went back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You never got into trouble when you were in the town school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No. The girls didn't seem to get - it's the boys are - a bit out of hand really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about things like tidiness and punctuality and manners and things like that at the town school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, yes, they - well they did try you know and - the few that used to - belt the hea
dmaster and the - the - one of the masters I was amazed at when I - saw that but he was a boy that was - mentally - but he went with a - one of the masters and scared me out of my life just for the moment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was there much roughness going on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well 
no, but he seemed this particular boy to be a tartar, they couldn't do much with him you know. They tried all sorts. But he would be very saucy you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you remember ever seeing sort of one or two people who were outsiders, never got on with 
anybody or were sort of ostracized by everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I don't think I did really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 In either school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No. I couldn't say that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You can't remember any one boy, a poor boy that the others used to bully?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, they weren't too
 bad like that, but this particular boy was - he was a bad tempered one and of course if the master went to chastise him he often - went for the master you see.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Why was that, why was he like that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I don't know whether it was his home training or what, you can't tell can you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have any gipsy boys or anything like that at the town school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, no, there was none of that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What did people think about gypsies in the neighbourhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well, they - they used to
 only pass through you know and - try and sell their laces and stuff at the door. But - we didn't get a lot of that really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What was the attitude, did anyone worry about them, that they might rob the house or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well no, I don't think 
they would do that really, but they used to get - they didn't like it if you didn't buy something and they'd say, you know - oh all your bad luck come your way and all this like they do you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You don't remember anything like somebody being made to leave the town by rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, no. No. I don't think it was ever so bad as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was there anybody in the district who the people disapproved of very strongly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. Well - not that I know of. No. It was a very placid community really you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You didn't ever come into contact with the parish charities or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I don't - I don't know that there was one. Whether there was such a thing I don't know really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh well they liked to see our homework and that you know, but - me mother wasn't - well she liked - she would see our work, but we didn't get a terrible lot of homework, but -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You got some home work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, yes, we got some homework. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of homework would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, only just the ordinary - write a composition on something you know. Nothing very outstanding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you do exams?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, they did exams, term exams you know. Yes, we didn't do bad at the term exams. I wouldn't say we're outstanding but - you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have reports and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes. Yes. We had reports at the girls school but I don't know that we did at the other school. I suppose we must have done. I'm not sure about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You'd be quite old, you'd be twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What were you thinking of doing when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
I didn't know. No. I didn't know because I was quite good at school, and I think I might have gone on for teaching - if my father had lived. You kno
w. But of course everything stopped then when he died you see, and then it was too late when our mother married again. So - I was seventeen you see and I went in - in the shop in Torpoint.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I suppose you would have regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 We
ll I - I think now - I don't mean now exactly but I mean ten years ago or twenty years ago perhaps, I might have thought - I would have done different had my father lived, you know, I should have taken up my -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 But you think you got something out of attending school even so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh I - yes, I think that. I - I - I think you - certainly improve with having decent schooling don't you. And possibly - I would have done very well if I'd gone on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Had your mother and father gone to a good school before?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh I don't - I don't think so, I - I don't know really. I expect they went to the schools in Torpoint. I don't know really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 In the town school did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from others, were there any favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I - they were very fair - I think, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about in the girls school, the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 And I think they were very fair there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were there any sort of gangs or little groups of people in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No I don't think so, they sort 
of - all - you know, joined in anything and were quite happy even everybody. I don't think I had any - much in my school days that I didn't think was very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How old would you be when you left the town school, fifteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Oh fourteen perhaps. Fifteen, between fourteen and fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 And you had to leave then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well then I - I left, I knew I wasn't going to do anything by staying at school. And I went into a shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was it the normal thing to sort of stay at school that long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, it wasn't really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What time did they normally leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well they did - they went in businesses and the boys went in the dockyard or joined the Navy. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you do any part time education courses afterwards, like evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No I didn't. Not so far back as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I don't suppose you had a part time job while you were still at school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, not while I was still at school but when I - left school - well I - I - I went into the local Food Office to help
, you know, with the - what would that be, the food rat - no - ration books was it in the first world war?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You'd leave school when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, 14 you see. No, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No - I was fourteen when I left. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That would be about 1911?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, no. Let me think. You'd better switch that off a minute while I'm thinking had you? Then I left school and went in a shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It was a food shop was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 A food shop. Yes. And I was there until I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Until 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Right through the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was it just a little shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes, in Torpoint, a cake shop. Mm. Well that is when I used to go - up to the Food Office, so that was the first world war wasn't it. Now what did I do then? What did I do then? Not there then, what was it, ration books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would this be while you were still working in the cake shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, in the bakery shop, because the - the - the food - chap came in and asked me if I'd come up and do some evening work. And two of us
 went up. Must have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What did you have to do in the cake job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh just sell the cakes there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of hours did you have to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh - let me see, let me - nine in the morning 'til seven. And it was eight -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Nine in the morning 'til seven o'clock at night?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It's a long day isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, but still - and - there's none - no five o'clock time then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I suppose shop jobs especially would be long because as you say the shop owners were trying to get as much as they could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh of course they did, yes, yes, this was an owner too that I worked for. So he liked to stay open as long as he could you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What was it on Saturdays did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Nine. Eight or nine, all depends if we sold out sometimes he would say I could go home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So you'd be working twelve hours on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have a half day during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Wednesday afternoons they used to close. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What did your other sisters do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh - they were in bus - she was in business my older sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
She was a - well you wouldn't know the store now but it's - it's a Plymouth departmental store. Or Devenport actually. Mm. Well that was the drapery, drapery hers was. Y
ou know, the - well everything departmental store, you know like - like - Plymouth shops do, sell everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How did you get this job in the cake shop, who got that for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh - no, I went myself. He was - the girl that was leaving I knew and -
 getting married and then she said what about you having my job, which I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you want to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, I rather liked it. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have to work on a Sunday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you say you had a half day at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, half a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What day of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Wednesdays - he used to shut.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you get paid during that half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Yes. Well I started with ten shillings a week and - by the time I got married I got a pound and that was a terrific wage. It was,
 a pound a week, my word I was lucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You were working very long hours for it weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 They didn't take notice of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would you get any paid holidays with this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, I suppose I must have. I think I had a week's holiday. Must have had a week's holiday mustn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you get paid for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about Bank Holidays, would you get those off as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh we - yes, well, yes, he shut Bank Holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It's not very much is it for all the hours you had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh that didn't - take notice of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you give the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well it wasn't enough - well it used to go in you know, I think I used to get me two bob out of the ten you know, sort of like that, but then she used to buy me clothes you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What would you spend it on, the money you had yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - we couldn't go anywhere so just in the sweetshop you know and or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you feel it was a fair wage what you got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, I was - I was
 quite happy when I went there when he said ten shillings I thought well that's good. I think I got me tea - as - from there. 'Cos I - I worked you see after tea, seven o'clock, so I think you - he had to give me me tea for - for keeping me the hours you 
see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That wouldn't be a sort of high tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh no, no, just - a boiled egg sometimes he used to give me. Well the - the wife did. I used to have that at the back of the shop, I didn't - go into the house and have it you know, I didn't get any time o
ff for it. Used to work - eat it between customers you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How did you get on with your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh very well indeed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 He was one of the local traders was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did he treat you OK?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Very well. He was always very civil.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 There was just him and you was there working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
No, the wife - was there, but she was - he had two shops, I had the cake shop - by myself, and he was - used to work in the grocery side across the road, with his wife. He had the two shops then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did he bake his own bread and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes, the - we used to have a baker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You didn't have to help with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, that was - in -- in the back of the - well not quite - in the back of the shop but
 next door, I never come in contact with that. He - the baker used to bring the bread in and I used to stack it you see and sell it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You did that until you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You didn't do any jobs after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would you have preferred another type of occupation perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, it was not - done - nobody ever looked for a job after we got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about before you got married, would you have preferred another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I was quite happy because I knew that I was courting and I wasn't going to be there very long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You were courting before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, yes, more or less you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So girls really thought in terms of getting married more than careers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - you see, the thing was I was engaged to someo
ne else for a long time, and then I met my husband and I - met him at Christmas and I was engaged in April and married in September, of the same year, so - that was it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Before that you'd had this other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well running round with him sort of thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You didn't have to serve an apprenticeship or training period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you belong to any trade union or professional organization?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, I did never see him after I left the shop. I - I think he - I don't know what he used to do. I used to go home of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 He didn't sort of 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 A sort of a friendship basis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, no, he was quite the
 - boss you know. He was quite satisfied with what I did I think because I took it on - my own to do a bit of buying in the sweets and stuff you know. But as I say it wasn't many years that I was there really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you sort of feel on a par}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well, yes. Yes. Of course I - I always - you know, I didn't - enter any - like general conversation with him a lot. He would just come in of a morning and say to you, everything all right, and that was that. He didn't want me - he knew as the - the - t
he takings were what they should be and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you think full time work changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well I used to see a lot more people you see. And I knew most people that came in the shop. That makes a difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You think you natured a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, well I was twenty then you see. Getting on you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did it change your way of life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I used to do much the same. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You wouldn't have more freedom, you'd have less hours in fact wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes
, I didn't have a lot of time and then I - used to - take my finance home with me, he used to meet me at the shop and go home with me. Go for a walk, that's all we did you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You continued living at home right through 'til you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Until I was married, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. No. She was quite happy because I was in the district - in - in Torpoint you see, I used to - I didn't come to Plymouth to work.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 But did she think you perhaps were more responsible, wouldn't need looking after so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, she - she didn't worry very much, she used to - you know, we used to be friends you see as ever, as we got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you spend Sundays any differently at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well no I didn't really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You still went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well I - I went to the church until I - the children come along and - and then I took them you know as they got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about Sunday school, would you go to that after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, I didn't, I left Sunday school you see. 'Cos I had me own home then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about while you were still living with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Yes, I kept that up while I was in the business. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were there anything like Girl Guides?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, there was no Guides. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about Salvation Army, did they ever come round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes, no, they didn't - there was no Salvation Army in Ply - in Torpoint. There was a - a section in Plymouth I think, but - we didn't come in contact with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you come into contact at all with the Plymouth Brethren?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. We didn't actually. 'Cos that isn't a very wide sect is it really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I just wondered 'cos it's got the name Plymouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes? No, it isn't. It's - a - I think that's only a name actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So you would sort of use your spare time in roughly the same way as when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 In much the same way, yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. Didn't have enough brains f
or that. Well it wasn't - no, it - it's amazing - that - politics didn't enter - our lives very much, not like today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have any views at all do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, no, I - I don't - I wouldn't like to say that I did. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You weren't allowed to vote in general elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever sort of feel any pressure from your employer to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, he didn't ever - discuss any of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You wouldn't take part in any election activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, no, I didn't do any of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever go out in the evenings, when you were working, before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well not much because I worked 'til I - it was - seven o'clock and I had to go and have me - you know, bits and pieces.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, boyfriends you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When did you first start going out with the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 There's a thing to ask. Have you got that thing on now? Oh my gosh. Well we always used to be able to run around with th
e boys a bit you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 There was no sort of strictness on the side of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, as long as we were in at nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh we'd go walks, or socials - perhaps at the church sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would they be at night time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, but not too late. Or else I wouldn't be allowed to go you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever meet any friends through work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, because I didn't - only worked - there was a couple of girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you bring friends home at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well me boyfriends used to come in sometimes but - not - not too often, wouldn't have that too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So your mother would meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, she knew them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have any sort of special girlfriends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well, yes, schoolgirls you know, but not a lot really, because - we had - I - I actually was going with somebody so long you know what I mean when I was sixteen 'til twenty really, that I didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did this change the way you dealt with your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh yes, well yes, I used to go out with - him rather than me sisters you see. So that - they had to make their own - way. Fifty-two. Fifty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Fifty-one that year you say you've been married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, 1919, 1969, 70, 71.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When did your husband die?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Three years now - in October. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How long had you known your husband when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh about one year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh we went to a whist drive and dance and - he came home from abroad, and - that was it you
 see. He'd been away a couple of years, I didn't know him. But he came over and - spoke and there you are and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where did he come from, do you know?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh he came from - foreign parts, he was in the Navy you see. His family did live in Torpoint but I didn't know them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 But he was sort of a local boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh - well yes, Plymouth boy really - born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What was the distance between your homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well, yes, because he lived about - oh half an hour from me I suppose actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That's quite a way in those days then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Well he used to - he used to walk - maybe not quite a half an hour but - say twenty minutes then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 But you didn't know him really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you write letters to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, because I didn't meet him 'til he came back you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So he didn't go away during the time you were courting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No. He'd just come back from two and a half years you see in China.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What was the arrangement then, you met him and then you got engaged straight away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes, and we were married in the September.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You met him when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 January.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Could, you remember the first time that you met his parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Actually he had no parents then. Oh his father was alive then, yes. But his mother - died when he was thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How old was he when you first met him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well he was twenty-seven when we got married. So it was still twenty-seven wasn't it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How old were you, about twenty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Twenty-one. Between twenty and twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you remember the first occasion when you first went into his father's home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - not long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you arrange it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, well he wanted me to see his sister because she brought him up after his mother died you see. And it w
as only his sister and his father. And - the sister's husband you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was there any special reason for taking you home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, only that I didn't know them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It wasn't to announce the engagement or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well they knew that we were going to get engaged you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How soon after was it when you met him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, I - I met him in January and I was engaged in April and married in September.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 But how soon after meeting him was it that you first went round to his home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh, a few weeks that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did they ask any sort of questions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, because his sister had seen me in - in the business that I worked you see. I used to serve her as a customer you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you know her sort of on first name terms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. Not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of home did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh, quite nice. You know, like our own really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It was like your own house really?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, very similar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What did his father do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 He was - in the Navy but - of course I did
n't know him then. He had retired years from the Navy when I met them at all. Because the old boy was getting on you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What was your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291 fianc\'e9\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291  job in the Navy at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 He was a Chief PO when we got married. Then he rose - to - you know, through the ranks until he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You can't remember what his father did before he retired from the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh he's a Naval man but I - I don't know much about him really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you remember whether your husband was brought up to go to the church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, the church - Church of England he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you often go to his home after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, we used to - regularly go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you treated as one of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh very much so, yes, they were very very - fond of me really although I say it myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you allowed to talk together by yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, well we had plenty of time together anyway, either - my home or his home or when we went out together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How did you get on with your parents in law after you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh very well. Yes. Very well indeed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How often did you see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, we used to - call in you know or go there for a cup of tea. In fact we've been almost like one family, all of us you know. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When you got married in September 1917 you moved?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 We moved into a flat in Torpoint then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was that near to where his father lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Not too far, not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever go round and help with odd jobs and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, well he - they - they didn't need him but if - they wanted anything he would do it, but he didn't do any - jobs really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What did you call them before marriage, did you call him father or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh mum and dad you know. Both of them - of course he didn't have a mother himself, bu
t his father used to call his own father father you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What did you all him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Dad. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 The same after marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you remember the first time that he met your parents, or your stepfather and mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, my - his father-in-law, my father - my stepfather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 When your husband first met your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well I took him home then you see. Well they didn't know him you see at all. Well they - they thought he was quite a nice young chap.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was it a sort of scheduled appearance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh no, I had to - I said, can I bring him in you see. You know, this - this is the - it isn't like today you know. No, no, he didn't turn up with a sleeping bag. Oh my no. Oh no, he was duly invited in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did they want to know about what he was doing for a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh they - they knew he - he - he wore Naval uniform so they knew that he was in the Navy you see. And as - my father and my stepfather were Navy people so they thought the everybody that was in the Navy were quite vetted you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was this the first boy you'd taken home to meet your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no. Oh no. Taken two or three home before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did they ever warn you off certain others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - 'course they thought I was too young, I - they didn't want
 me to get - they weren't mad about me getting married when I did really, but they - made a very nice do for me you know but - they thought was plenty soon enough you see. Because they said I didn't know him you see very long. But still it worked out very
 well in the end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Now how long did you go out with the other one that you were engaged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh - from school almost. Well for - yes, it was a long time really, too long. Just fizzled out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did they encourage him at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, yes, they - liked him very much, yes, until the end and they didn't think that - he took me for granted too much they said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your parents know his before you started courting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Now did they first meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well actually they didn't really meet ver
y much I don't think, I - think he met his - my parents met his sister, but they never visited or anything like that until I got married and they came to the wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So they sort of met more or less at the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well they might have met a bit before but nothing - startling, they didn't visit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did they have to go through many arrangements together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no, we fixed that up ourselves you know with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did they see much of each other after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Not - they did
n't see a lot, his - his sister used to call to see my mother because of course she was younger that my mother - but - they were all happy together you know although they didn't see much of each other.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 But as you say going out visiting friends and relatives just wasn't done so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It wasn't done so much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How often did you see each other when you first started courting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, most - two or three times a week or more, when he was on duty you see 'cos - with the Navy they got to do s
o much duty, night duteis and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of things would you do together at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh let me see, what did we do? Well - we didn't do a lot really because we were getting our place together and that, and - then we had - well what did we do? We - we had the family started you know, after what - 1920.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh well, we just - met each other and - came to Plymouth sometimes to the pictures. Because we were together then you see, it wasn't like me coming on my own. We 
- used to come over to the pictures - into Devonport which wasn't very far then, but - I think that's all gone now out there, where it used to be the pictures you know. And we'd go to walks and we used to - in the summertime - 'cos there was only one summ
er but - he was very keen on boating, and we used to go out in a boat of an evening you know, up and down the - Tamar and that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did he row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Canoe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about bike riding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, well he didn't bike, I - I had a bike but I got rid of it. But he never cycled very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So this was the kind of thing that happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well yes. It was a short time you see that we didn't do a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you keep going out with groups of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No. He used to come home to my place and I used to go out to his sister's of an evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You'd go out together rather than in a group?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, we just went - out to his place and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you ever get a chance to go on holidays during your courtship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Wel
l not together, I - I'd previous - before I met him I was going with an aunt of mine - because they had no children and I went with them and - of course as it was arranged I still went. Well he came - with - not with me, he came to me for a week, I went f
or a fortnight and he came up for one week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 But he - Ilfracombe, but he stayed in another hotel because of course we - my aunt had booked up - for us previous to that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you remember the moment when you decided to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well no because I was - he was - keeping on to get married and of course I - wasn't I didn't want to get married quite so soon but you see he had no home, well he lived with his sister which - it was his sister and husband and his father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 His sister's husband was there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Yes. So that he was anxious to make a home of his own you see. So - well as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 sk}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
on as we - got engaged we were looking round to get a flat you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 So he'd be the one who said will you marry me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, oh we got to get married you see, we - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did he keep on going on about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
He was always very keen to get married because he'd been away two and a half years and he had a bit of money saved you see, that he had nothing to wait for you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did it come as a surprise when he asked you to marry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh no, I thought that was what he was on upon, you know, well I knew the circumstances that he was living - he was perfectly happy with them but then when he was twenty-seven he thought he'd like to get married you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did he ask your parents permission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
No, he didn't. Well he did say well we thought about getting married, what do you think about it? 'Cos - my mother thought it was a bit soon but - it worked out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you present at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, I was there waiting to hear what they said, but I thought well whatever they say, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you tell your parents before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well they had an idea there was something, because they knew that he
 was - just come home from abroad and that he didn't want to wait, you see, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 But you were engaged beforehand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 We were engaged just three months, or three or four months you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Do you think you can be engaged without a ring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well you can be but I was very proud of the ring I had anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Can you describe any of the rings you had before marriage, did your husband have one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, we got - we gave each other a wedding ring on our wedding day - actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 He didn't have an engagement ring before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No, he didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have one before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Was there an announcement in the paper that you were engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No it wasn't done in them days like it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What about a party or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No we didn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You wouldn't have any presents then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. I - and that was a thing that's - something new, fairly new, this engagement parties and engagement presents and various you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your parents treat you both any differently once you were engaged?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have to be in by a certain time still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Well - they didn't say much, because it was summer you see. That we didn't - in fact we weren't out - used to be out late then unless we - went anywhere and then the last house of the pictures was always finished by half past nine or ten. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were you left alone together a bit more than you might have been beforehand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well no, I don't think we were really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How did you choose your wedding ring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh well we both came and bought that. Into Plymouth you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Not very long before the wedding or just before the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh - a week or two you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who paid for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh he did, I didn't have any money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Have you had any rings since marriage, like an eternity ring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Yes, and I've had it all stolen from here. Me engagement ring and all, yes. Just after my - husband died - it happened, they broke in here while I was at church on the following Sunday after he was bur
ied. So I think they knew that I was out you see and - oh they took all sorts, my record player and - all my jewelry and my sister's jewelry and - that she lived with me you see when she was ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 This is your eldest sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes. Very unfortunate. So that actually -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you exchange any t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291 hings like love tokens, valentin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 es?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, nothing like that really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you save up before getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well he was away two and a half years you see. So he'd saved the money. Yes. He had the money.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you find a house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 We had a flat for the twelve months and then we got a house of our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you look for a flat before you decided to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well actually it was my uncle's house. And he said I could have it because 
he had a job in the - dockyard and there was a house found on the terrace in the dockyard for the job that he had. So he said, if you like to have my house until you can get something, but I shall be coming back in twelve months time, so that gave us the 
time to look around for our house you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you know about that before you decided to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well no, we were - we - it - it happened about the same time, that's why we - offered - he offered it to us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you buy any household equipment before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No, I don't think we did really. Because you see we had nowhere to put it anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did your parents help you in setting up home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No, they didn't need to really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have a bottom drawer or a trousseau?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I don't think he had very much, I had my bits and pieces you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What kind of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well, my bedding and underclothes and all that extra stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who did you first see to arrange about the wedding, the vicar or somebody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well yes, I suppose it would be wouldn't it really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Would you get married in the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well - the Methodist church where I was brought up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 In the Methodist rather than the Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes, well I was the Methodist you see so he - he became a Methodist, he came to chapel with me after. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How long before the wedding did you go along to fix it up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well - what - I don't know, week or two I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Quite soon before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well you didn't have
 to - have - so long - in those days as they do now. And of course they - had receptions in - in the - hotels and cafes and stuff now different wo what they did in my day, 'cos we only had the - few friends at home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 You didn't have a lavish sort of spread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. No. There was only his family and mine. And the - Methodist minister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Were there any particular reasons for the wedding date you chose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 No. Only that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Who chose it, you or him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well me I expect - but - you know, when we could fix it up we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 What day did you get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Twenty-fourth of September, 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 I suppose you chose the Methodist church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 That was my church, yes, I wouldn't have gone anywhere else you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 It was a religious ceremony then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have any difficulty getting your parents agreement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh no, no, they were quite happy about it all. I expect they had their little say because they didn't think I was old enough and after that they dropped it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you want a small wedding, you say it was only family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
Oh - oh he didn't - he didn't worry too much, he - he didn't - he said, well that's you please yourself and you'll please me you see. Mm. I don't like a lot of show - really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How did you decide who to invite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Well it was only both sides actually. And after that - one or two friends I suppose but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Did you have any relations, apart from his sister and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Yes, well - then there was - no only the immediate relations. Of
 course all the friends of mine came to the church and - well in fact we had lots in the chapel, because of course I was brought up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 How many guests do you think there would be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14811249 D  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 Oh - oh I suppose there may be about - twenty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16275245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 On each}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14945689\charrsid14952291  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7951666\charrsid14952291 
side?
